Hey Bob,

I just wanted to send a quick note about our weekend hiking trip to Pine Ridge Trail. It was such a beautiful spot—lush greenery, winding streams, and plenty of wildflowers in bloom. I really appreciated your company and all the laughs along the way.

On Saturday morning we set off early to catch the sunrise at Eagle Point. The view was breathtaking! We even spotted a family of deer grazing near the ridge. After that, we stopped by Clear Lake for a picnic lunch. Your homemade sandwiches were a hit—especially the pesto turkey ones.

Sunday’s stretch was challenging but rewarding. Climbing up the eastern slope gave us quite the workout, and I’m proud of how well we kept each other motivated. The final lookout point offered a panoramic view of the valley below—definitely worth the effort.

Thank you again for joining me. I’ve attached my photos from the trip to a shared folder in case you want to download any. Let me know when you’re free next month; I’m already scouting new trails for our next adventure!

Happy trails,
